Grant Park is Ideally located in the thriving East Town area of downtown Minneapolis; walk or bike to the new Vikings Stadium, Nicollet Mall & all your favorite entertainment venues surrounding you! A great community to enjoy Downtown Living!

description:
Recently sold: $100,000. I'm looking for someone to move in September 15th or October 1st! Remodeled one-bedroom condo overlooking Eat Street in the high demand Whittier Neighborhood. Located minutes to downtown and uptown and 2 blocks from one of the hottest areas in Minneapolis -- Ice House, Vertical endeavors, Cooper Hen, Eat Street Social. . . excellent places to eat, arts, and entertainment. This is the new uptown -- even Cheapo Records decided to pack up and move here. It is also within walking distance to MCAD, MIA, The Walker, Loring Park. The condo itself is small but lovely. Built in 1904, it features classic Minneapolis woodwork, hardwood floors, exposed brick, high ceilings, claw foot bathtub, and modern amenities like a dishwasher and gas range. It has eastern and southern sun exposure, with the kitchen and living room overlooking Nicollet, and the bedroom shadowed by the adjacent building. The layout makes efficient use of space, accommodating a queen-sized mattress, and maximizing space with built-in closet storage. It is a 80% owner-occupied condominium, so the neighbors are quiet and considerate. It's going to feel more like a home than an apartment. I am the owner and I loved living here. I am only moving out to live with my partner. $1,100 rent includes heat, water, a storage 4'x10' storage unit in the basement, off-street parking, free laundry, and window A/C unit. For Minnesotans who need to stay warm in the winter, this is a good find. The building stays toasty. Tenant is responsible for electricity, gas, and WiFi. Electricity and gas for this unit are cheap (my annual average cost is $34.09/mo). The unit will be available September 1st or 15th. 1-2 year lease preferred.

Owner pays for water and heat. Tenant pays for electricity and gas.
